INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('1', '国外进口商向本国商务部咨询国外可合作伙伴', '18813192817@163.com', '', '{Commerce Department (of the US government)< 请填写欲征询的政府机构名称，如商务部Commerce Department，外经贸部MOFTEC(Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation), 俄罗斯大使馆Russian Embassy> }<br>\n[Thank you for your long-standing support! |<Thank you for your help from all aspects in these years.>|<Our co-operation has been very successful in a long period of time.>]<br>\nWe [sincerely|<genuinely>] hope to [expand our business|< broaden our business>|<establish our business >] in{all kinds of cotton products<请填写欲开展贸易的相关产品>}, but there are no ideal partners in{China<请填写欲开展贸易的国家或地区>}. [It will be appreciated |< We would be grateful>]that you provide us some information about {those companies who are professional and reliable in this line<请填写希望得到哪些相关信息>}, so that we can [establish business relationship|< establish cooperative relationship>|<build trade relationship>|<enter into business relations>] with them. <br>\n[We are looking forward your to early reply!|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.>|< Your early reply is appreciated.>|< We are anticipating your answer.>] <br>\nYours sincerely, <br>\n{American Cotton Company<请填写己方公司名称>}<br>\n', null, null, '××商务部: <br>\n感谢你们长期以来对我们的支持. <br>\n目前我们殷切希望能够扩大各种棉制品的贸易,但在中国地区尚没有理想的合作伙伴. <br>\n因此,请你们为我们介绍几家专业可靠,有实力的进口商,建立业务往来关系. <br>\n此致谢意,盼复. <br>\n美国棉织品总公司<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('2', '中国进口商致电波兰大使馆经济贸易处询问贸易信息', '', '', 'Dear Sirs，<br>\n[We have heard from|<We have learned through>|<We have your name and address from>] {Polish Embassy in China<请填写欲征询的政府机构名称，如俄罗斯驻中国大使馆Russian Embassy in China，商务部Commerce Department，外经贸部MOFTEC(Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation)>} that the Economic and Trade Office [dedicated to|<worked on>|<devoted to>] furthering communications between Poland and China by organizing business pavilions and publishing trade information. [Our company is in the Long-term operation of auto parts{<请填写相关贸易产品>}|< We wish to inform you that we specialize in {auto parts<请填写相关贸易产品>} >|<auto parts fall within our business activities >|< We have in the line of {auto parts<请填写相关贸易产品>} for many years >]. [As our company is expanding its business, we want to develop a new market in your market|< Because your market has a big potential demand for our products, we express our desire to enter into your market >]. [If you send us some information in this line for our reference, we will highly appreciate your kindly reply|< We shall be grateful if you will send us some information in this regard at an early date >]. <br>\nYours truly, <br>\n', null, null, '波兰大使馆经济贸易处：<br>\n从贵国驻中国大使馆得知，经济贸易处经常采用组织商务展团及商务交流，发布贸易信息等方式促进两国经济交流。我公司长期经营汽车配件，近年来由于业务扩大，希望能够在贵国开辟新的市场，若能在贵处获得该行业的贸易信息，我们将不胜感激。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('3', '向贸促会征询贸易信息', null, null, 'Dear Sirs，<br>\nWe all know that {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写欲征询机构名称（中国贸易促进委员会CCPIT，亦可替换成其他类似机构）>} [enjoys a high prestige among friendly companies and plays an irreplaceable role in the promotion of trade development|< is one of the most institutions which play a very important role in development of international trade >|< does a lot in strengthening the exchange of business between China and other counties >]. [Now we are approaching you with a view to get some industrial information to enlarge our business in { timber export trade<填写贸易范围> }|< As our company is expanding our business in{ timber export trade<填写贸易范围> }, we want to develop a new market in your market>|< Because your market has a big potential demand for{ timber export trade<填写贸易范围> }, we desire to get some information in this line >]. [Could you please let us be informed of some professional and reliable companies which in the business of {mahogany, rosewood, Spanish cedar<填写具体贸易产品>}?|< We would be very grateful if you can send us a list of leading companies doing business in {mahogany, rosewood, Spanish cedar<填写具体贸易产品>}.>] [Your kindly help will be appreciated! |< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.>|< Your early reply is appreciated.>|< We are anticipating your answer.>|< We are looking forward to your early reply!>]<br>\n', null, null, '敬启者：<br>\n我们都知道中国贸促会在促进贸易发展上发挥着不可替代的作用，在众多贸易公司中享有盛誉。特此致电，盼能获悉木材出口贸易方面的行业信息，以扩大我公司业务。希望能够从贵处取得一些从事桃花心木、红木、西班牙雪松贸易的专业可靠的公司信息。此致谢意,盼复. <br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('4', '向贸易展览会索要与会名单及相关参阅', '', '', 'Dir Sirs,<br>\n[We learn from |< We have your information from>]{Xiamen Daily<得知有展会的消息来源，如某某日报，某某网站等>} that {the coming 7th Xiamen International Stone Fair<展会的具体名称，表示展会的词汇有：Exhibition：general exhibition, industrial exhibition, agricultural exhibition, consumer exhibition, international exhibition, regional exhibition, local exhibition, private exhibition, major exhibition, minor exhibition, solo exhibition, peripatetic exhibition, exposition;Show： trade show, moveable show, road show, boat show, plane show, catalogue show;Fair： multi-trade fair, international ×× fair;Trade mart;Display… >}, for[businessmen at home and abroad|< domestic and oversea traders >], provides [an exchange platform|< a platform for communication >], by which [businessmen can take this rare opportunity to present their corporate images and expand markets|< businessmen can deeply introduce their companies and fully display their products>|<businessmen may discuss in detail face to face>], except making the acquaintance of copartners and [creation of business opportunity|< acquirement of new customers>|<development of new business relationship>]. So we expect to get a list of participating enterprises and other references for our preparation [in view of|< with the purpose of\n>]establishing more business chances. <br>\n[Your prompt reply will be appreciated!|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.>|<Your early reply is appreciated.>|<We are anticipating your answer.>|<We are looking forward to your early reply!>] <br>\n', null, null, '从厦门日报上得知，即将开幕的第七届中国（厦门）国际石材展览会，将会为国内外商家搭建国际贸易平台，在展示企业形象、拓展市场同时，帮助企业寻求合作伙伴和发展商机。因此，我们殷切希望能够获得参会企业的名单目录，以及与会要求，以便我公司能有针对性的做准备，进而能在此次展会中获得更多的贸易机会，结实更多的贸易伙伴。<br>\n欣盼早日惠复。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('5', '向总部咨询适合的分支机构', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>\nAfter years of mutual cooperation in the business of { shoes<填写贸易产品> }, [friendly relationship has been established between us|< we make an extensive and in-depth trade >]. Now [we have opened a new business branch|< our new affiliate has been established >] in{Qingdao at 126 Huanghai Rd. Canghai, Q. D.< 填写分支机构的地区及详细地址>}. [In order to continue|< With the purpose of continuing >|< For continuing >] our cooperation in this line, [would you like to fax us your branches in this district so that we can cope successfully with your company? |< we express our desire to have your branches’ information in this region in order that we can expand our business.>]<br>\nIf you will kindly send all information of your branches to that address, [we will promptly contact with your branches to further our cooperation|< we will timely build a closer partnership between us >] in{Qingdao<填写欲开展进一步合作的地区>}. <br>\n[Thank you for your fast favors.|< Your prompt reply will be appreciated!>|< We are anticipating your answer.>|< We are looking forward to your early reply!>] <br>\n                                                         Yours truly,<br>\n', null, null, '敬启者：<br>\n经过多年在鞋业的合作，你我公司之间以建立了友好的合作关系。现在我公司在青岛市黄海路沧海区又开立了新的分支机构，为了促进我们之间的进一步合作，贵公司可否传真给我方一些有关贵公司在青岛分支机构的情况。如果能收到贵公司寄来的宝贵信息，我们将第一时间与之联系开展合作。敬盼惠复！<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('6', '商务部', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs, < br >\n[From the information sent back by|< Receiving information from >] {the Commerce Department<请填写获知信息的来>}, we know that [you are handling {foodstuffs<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>} for export|<you specialize in {foodstuffs<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>}  for many year>|<{foodstuffs<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>} fall within your business activities >] and[we particularly interested in various {foodstuffs<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>} from your district|< we take the liberty to introduce ourselves as the biggest{foodstuffs<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>} importer in our country >|< we have imported {foodstuffs<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>}  from the companies in your district >]. [In view to establish business relationship|< In order to develop cooperative relationship >|< With the purpose of establishing trade relationship>] between our two companies, we are writing to you for getting your {catalog and other printed matters<请填写希望对方提供的材料>} for reference. < br >\n[We are looking forward to your earlier reply|< We look forward to your early reply with much interest >|< We look forward to receiving your positive response >].< br >\n\"\r\n', null, null, '根据从商务部获得的反馈信息，我方获悉贵方从事食品的出口贸易，对您所在地区出口的多种食品均感兴趣。着眼于建立贵我双方的贸易关系，盼能惠赐商品目录及相关材料以作参考。<br>\n烦请早日赐复。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('7', '大使馆', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs, < br >\n[We learn from {the British Embassy|<请填写获知信息的来源>} that|< We have your name and address from {the British Embassy|<请填写获知信息的来源>}that >|< On the recommendation of {the British Embassy|<请填写获知信息的来源>} we know that >] [you are producing for export {hand-made shoes and gloves in pure hide and other natural material<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>}|< you are in the line of {hand-made shoes and gloves in pure hide and other natural material<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>}>|<{hand-made shoes and gloves in pure hide and other natural material<请填写欲展开贸易的相关产品>} fall within our business activities >l. < br >\n[There is a steady demand here for high-class goods of this kind of products|< As the market shows an upward tendency, everyone who has requirements for the goods is rushing to make a purchase >|< Since supply still falls short of demand，the rising tendency of the price is naturally expected to continue for some time.>]. [Therefore we are approaching you to see if we can enter into business relations with you|< We are willing to establish business relations with your firm on the basis of equality and mutual benefit >|< We are writing to you in the hope that we can open up business relations with your firm >]. We hope to receive your {catalog and price list<请填写希望对方提供的材料，如产品目录catalog，价目表price list，样品sample等>} [for consideration |<or reference>]and [build up|< establish >] friendly relations between us. < br >\n[Your early reply will be appreciated.|< Your prompt reply will be appreciated!>|< We are anticipating your answer.>] < br >\nYours, < br >\n\"\r\n', null, null, '我方从英国大使馆获悉，贵方出口的鞋子和手套是以真皮和其他天然材料为原料手工生产的。<br>\n本地对于此类的高级产品有持续稳定的需求。因此，与贵公司联系企盼双方能建立贸易关系。我方希望获得贵方的产品目录及价目表以供审议并由此建立双方良好的关系。<br>\n希望早日收到您的回复。此致<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('8', '地区政府', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>\n[Your company has been recommended by|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] your government procurement as one of the [largest|< most famous >|< oldest >] exporters of {tea<请填写对方进行贸易的商品>} in {Fujian Province<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}. [We are also one of the firms of good standing in our country|< We are a stated-owned company having the right to import and export >|< We are specialized in the above business and recall that in these years, considerable business was done with other companies in your country >].[We feel confident that you can push the sale of our products in your market|< Our market survey informs us that you have a keen interest in the import of the above-mentioned goods >]. We would like to send you some {printed materials<请填写希望对方提供的材料>} for [building|< establishing >]a relationship between us. [If you place a trial order to test your market, we are rather sure that our products will meet-with your customers\' satisfaction|< We fully understand that you are a most selective buyer and therefore we leave it entirely to you to decide which style is most suitable for your requirements >|< Since then our annual sale has broken its own record every year. So, if you try them on your market, you will certainly have very handsome business >]. <br>\n[We are looking forward to your soon reply.|< Thank you for your fast favors. >|< Your prompt reply will be appreciated!>].<br>\nYours truly, <br>\n', null, null, '据贵地政府采购办向我们介绍,贵公司是福建地区的最大茶叶出口商。我们亦是国内信誉良好的商号之一，相信能将贵公司茶叶在我国市场上大力推广。如果你方能寄送一些产品相关的印刷品供我方参考，并由此建立贸易关系，我们将非常荣幸。如果你方的价格合适，我们将会下一笔大订单。尽盼惠复，谨上<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('9', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('10', '展览会', null, null, '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[Many thanks for your letter and enclosures of|< We have received your inquiry in >|< Thank you for your enquiry dated >] {12 September<请填写收到来函的日期>}. [We were very interested to hear that you are looking for {an UK distributor for your teaching aids<请填写对方函件提到期望开展的业务或贸易产品>}|< We are glad to know that you consider to expand your business in {an UK distributor for your teaching aids<请填写对方函件提到期望开展的业务或贸易产品>}>]. We would like to invite you to visit our booth, {No.6, at next month\'s London Toy Fair, at Earl\'s court, which starts on 2 October|<请填写邀请对方前去展会的日期、地点>}. If you would like to [set up an appointment|< have a discussion >|< hold a meeting >] during non exhibit hall hours please call me. [I can then arrange for our senior staff to be present at the meeting|< I can arrange the time convenient to you >]. [We look forward to hearing from you|< We are awaiting your early reply >|< Please mail us at your earliest convenience >]. <br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '多谢9月12日的来信和附件。获悉贵公司有意物色英国销售商推广教学辅助设备，甚感兴趣。本公司将于10月2日于厄尔大楼举行的伦敦玩具商品交易会上展示产品，诚邀贵公司派员参观设于6号之摊位。如能安排于非展出时间面谈，烦请电复。定必委派高层人员赴会。本公司深知贵公司产品精美质优，希望能发展互惠之业务。特此奉告，并候复音。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('15', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('16', '资信证明', '', '', 'REPORT ON THE HEBEI INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT COMPANY<br>\nThis is a report on {the Hebei Industrial Development Co., Ltd<请填写被征信公司名称>}. [About which you inquired in your letter of {March 20, 2008<请填写对方来函时间>}|< With the purpose of replying your letter of  {March 20, 2008<请填写对方来函时间>}, we prepare this document>]. We are pleased to [send|< provide >|< offer >] you the following [information|< document >|< material >|< data >]. <br>\n1. {This firm was established by WangJun in 2002<请填写被征信公司的成立时间>}. <br>\n2. {It operates as a wholesaler of motorcycle parts which is distributed throughout China<请填写被征信公司的业务范围>}. <br>\n3. {The net worth is in excess of RMB6,000,000<请填写被征信公司的净资产状况>}. <br>\n4. {The annual business turns over RMB10,000,000<请填写被征信公司的年营业额>}. <br>\n5. {Our records show that they have never failed to meet our bills since they opened an account with us in July 2003. The monthly limit of credit we feel that we may safely grant them is approximately RMB 1,000,000<请填写被征信公司的信用及支付记录>}. <br>\n[The managing staff of the company is well known to us|< The senior managers of the company have a good reputation in this district >|< The administrators of company are capable and creative >] and they [have high regard for|< pay close attention to >] their character, integrity and reliability, <br>\nWe hope that this information ⑹will be of assistance|< will be helpful >|< can help you make decisions >]. <br>\n', null, null, '关于河北工业发展公司报告<br>\n这是关于贵方2008年3月20日来函询问河北工业发展有限公司的报告。我方十分高兴地告知贵方一下信息：<br>\n1、这家公司由王军在2002年创立；<br>\n2、该公司从事摩托车零部件批发经营，在全国各地设有经销商；<br>\n3、净资产超过600万元；<br>\n4、年营业额超过1000万元；<br>\n5、记录显示自2003年该公司在我行开设账户以来，从未拖欠我方债务。我方授予该公司的月度信用额大约为100万元。<br>\n我方十分熟悉该公司的管理人员，他们具有正直、可靠的品质。<br>\n希望以上信息对贵方有帮助。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('18', '进口商请求担任独家代理', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n [We would like to inform you that we act on a sole agency basis for a number of manufacturers|< As publishers and distributors of over twenty years, we have a thorough knowledge of the market.>|< We wonder to give you the information that we have highly reputed as a large dealer in our country.>]. [We specialize in {finished cotton goods<请填写进口商的业务范围或主营产品>}|< We are in the line of {finished cotton goods<请填写进口商的业务范围或主营产品>}>|< {finished cotton goods<请填写进口商的业务范围或主营产品>} fall within our business >]for {the Middle eastern<请填写主要销售地区>} market. [Until now,|< Up to now>|< So far >] we have been working with your {textiles department<请填写与对方公司合作的业务部门>} and our [collaboration|< trade >|< business>] has proved to be [mutually beneficial.|< promising >|< potential>] [Please refer to them for any information regarding our company.|< The detail information about business between us please contact the department.>] [We are very interested in an exclusive arrangement with your factory for the promotion of your products|< We hope to hear from you and are desire of the possibility of representing you >] in {Bahrain. <请填写担任独家代理后的主要销售市场>} <br>\n [We look forward to your early reply.|< We trust you will give us an early reply.>|< We are expecting a reply at your earliest convenience.>] <br>\n                                                     Yours sincerely，<br>\n', '', '', '本公司担任多家厂家的独家代理，专营精制棉织品，行销中东。与贵公司向有业务联系，互利互作。贵公司纺织部亦十分了解有关业务合作之情况。盼望能成为贵公司独家代理，促销在巴林市场的货品。上述建议，烦请早日赐复，以便进一步联系合作。 **谨上<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('19', '接受代理请求', '', '', '[Thank you for your letter of {12 April<请填写对方寄来的上封函电时间，便于对方查看>} proposing a sole agency for {our office machines.< 请填写欲担任独家代理的商品名称>}|< We welcome your inquiry of {12 April<请填写对方寄来的上封函电时间，便于对方查看>}  and thank you for your interest in {our office machines.< 请填写欲担任独家代理的商品名称>}>|< Your inquiry for proposing a sole agency for {our office machines.< 请填写欲担任独家代理的商品名称>} has been received on {12 April<请填写对方寄来的上封函电时间，便于对方查看>} >] We have [examined|< reviewed>|< looked back>] our long and mutually beneficial [collaboration.|< cooperation>|< trade >|< business>] [We would be very pleased to entrust you with the sole agency for {Bahrain.< 请填写同意对方担任独家代理的区域范围>}|< We have approved your proposal to act as our agent in {Bahrain.< 请填写同意对方担任独家代理的区域范围>}>|< After careful consideration，we have decided to entrust you with the sole agency for our office machines in {Bahrain.< 请填写同意对方担任独家代理的区域范围>}>]<br>\n[We have drawn up a draft agreement that is enclosed. Please examine the detailed terms and conditions and let us know whether they meet with your approval.|< Please go over the enclosed draft agreement and let us have your comments by return.>][We are delighted that we are probably going to strengthen our relationship.|< We are confident that sole agency agreement will add a new page to the records of our cooperation.>] [We look forward to your early reply.|< We look forward to your trial order.>|< Your early reply to this inquiry is requested.>] <br>\n\n', '', '', '4月12日建议担任办公室器具之独家代理来信已经收悉。 过去双方合作皆互利互助，能获您的眷顾作我公司于巴林的独家代理，殊感荣幸。现随信附上协议草稿， 请查实各项条款 ，惠复是盼。能加强业务，我方甚感欣喜。祈盼您的早日回复。 <br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('20', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('21', '出口商拒绝对方担任独家代理', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[Thank you for your letter of|< We have received your inquiry of>|< Thank you for your inquiry dated>] {1 September<请填写对方寄来的上封函电时间，便于对方查看>} suggesting that we grant you a sole agency for {our household linens<请填写欲担任独家代理的商品名称>}. [I regret to say that, at this stage, such an arrangement would be rather premature|< We cannot give you exclusive agency for this territory without having a clear idea of the possible turnover you can make annually.>|< It would be better for us to leave the question of agency in abeyance until the opportunity presents itself.>|< As we are not yet thoroughly acquainted with each other, we think the time is not ripe for a discussion on agency.>]. We would, however, be willing to engage in a trial collaboration with your company to see how the arrangement works. It would be necessary for you to test the market for our products at your end. [You would also have to build up a much larger turnover to justify a sole agency|< We shall take up the matter of agency with you as soon as the business between us has developed to our mutual satisfaction. >|< Please redouble your efforts to build a large turnover so as to qualify for our sole agency appointment.>]. We enclose {price lists covering all the products you are interested in <请填写随附物品，如报价单、产品目录、样品等>}and [look forward to hearing from you soon|< hope to receive your favorable news soon.>|< are anticipating your answer.>]. <br>', '', '', '9月1日有关建议担任家用亚麻制品独家代理的来信收悉。谨致衷心谢意。目前时机尚未成熟，不能应允该安排深感抱歉。 然而，本公司乐意与贵公司先试行合作，为今后合作打下基础。为证明担任独家代理的能力，贵公司宜就上述货品作市场调查，研究是否可扩大现有之营业额。奉上该货品之报价单，敬希查照。专此候复。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('22', '寻找代理', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs，<br>\nWe have decided to [expand our business to {Japan<请填写相关国家或地区，在此区域寻找代理商>}|< enter into {Japan<请填写相关国家或地区，在此区域寻找代理商>} market>|< establish {Japan<请填写相关国家或地区，在此区域寻找代理商>} market>]. We are therefore looking for an agent with [an efficient sales organization|< well-established connections>|< a reliable firm with good connections>] in that [area| < district > |   < rigion > | ] to help us to market our products of {handmade shoes<请填写相关国家或地区，在此区域寻找代理商>}.<br>\n[We would be grateful if you could|< Could you>] introduce our name to your correspondents in {Japan<请填写相关国家或地区，在此区域寻找代理商>} and help us to get in touch with some suitable and reliable firms. <br>\n[Hope to hear from you soon|< We look forward to hearing from you promptly >|< Your early reply is highly appreciated >].<br>\nSincerely, <br>\n\"\r\n', '', '', '我方决定扩大在日本的经营。因此，我方正在该地区寻找一个有效率的销售代理商，帮助推广我方手工鞋。\n 如果能将我方公司名称告诉贵方在日本的联络人员，帮助我方与合适、可靠的公司接触，我方将十分感激。\n 期盼您早日回函。<br>\n\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('23', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('24', '接受寄售请求', '', '', 'Dear Sirs: <br>\n[We were pleased to receive your letter of {July 5th. < 请填写对方来函时间>}|< Thank you for your letter of>|< We have received your inquiry of>] [After a careful consideration of your terms, we have decided to accept your proposal that {we send you a trial delivery of our shoes on consignment.< 请填写我方接受对方提出的何种要求>}|< our suggestion that {we send you a trial delivery of our shoes on consignment.< 请填写我方接受对方提出的何种要求>} is acceptable under present market condition.>]We are therefore sending you {a representative selection of our most popular lines.< 请填写决定寄售何种产品>} The consignment is being shipped by {S.S. Angel<请填写寄售的承运船只>}, leaving {Dalian port for Inchon South Korea on July 30th.< 请填写出发、达到港及出发日期>} [We will send you bill of lading and other shipping documents as soon as we receive them.|< After we receive bill of lading and other shipping document, we will send them to you as soon as possible. <br>\n>] [In this letter, we are enclosing a pro forma invoice showing prices at which the goods should be offered for sale|< Enclosed please find our pro forma invoice showing prices at which the goods are to be offered for sale.>|< We are forwarding to you consignments, which please dispose of as advantageously as possible.>].[We hope you will find a ready sale for our products.|< We hope you will find our product stable for your market.>] <br>\nWith best regards, <br>\nYours, <br>\n', '', '', '很高兴收到贵方7月5日来函。经认真考虑贵方所提条件，我方决定接受贵方要求，向您尝试寄售我方生产的鞋子。\n因此，我方向贵方寄出几个最流行款式的产品。由天使号货船承运，7月30号由大连港发往韩国仁川。我方将尽快向贵方发送提单及其他货运单据。随信附上形式发票，以供您参考产品销售价格。<br>\n期盼贵方为我方产品找到销路。<br>\n    此致<br>\n敬礼<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('25', '经销商', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[Thank you for your letter of {May 5th.< 请填写收到来函的时间>}|< We have received your inquiry of>|< Thank you for your inquiry dated>][By this letter, we now formally authorize you to act as our distributor in|< After careful consideration, we have decided to entrust you with the our distributor in>|< We have approved your proposal to act as our distributor in>] {Hangzhou China. <请填写授予经营权的地区>} Enclosed are two copies each of the following documents: <br>\n1. Authorization file<br>\n2. Catalogue and technical data<br>\n[Please sign and return us the duplicate copy of this letter|< This letter should be signed by you and returned to us>], together with one copy each of the [above|< mentioned>] documents. [We look forward to a pleasant business relationship.|< We are confident that entrusting you with distributor will add a new page to the records of our cooperation.>|< We trust that you will see your way to grant us substantial orders.>] <br>\nYours sincerely, <br>\n', '', '', '感谢贵方5月5日来函。<br>\n 通过这封信函，我方正式授予你方在中国杭州作为我方的经销商。随函附寄以下文件的复印件两份：<br>\n1、授权文件；<br>\n2、产品目录和技术数据。<br>\n请签署并寄回这封函件的复印件，以及上述文件一份。期望与贵方建立良好的商业关系。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('26', '进口商向出口商索要商品目录及报价表', '', '', 'Dear Gentlemen: <br>\n[We have obtained your name and address from|< We have obtained the information of your company from>|< We have learned through>] {Aristo Shoes, Milan<请填写信息来源，如：报纸广告、电视广告、老客户关系等>} , and [we are writing to enquire whether you would be willing to establish business relations with us.|< we are will to enter into business relations with you.>|< we are writing to you in the hope that we can open up business relations with your firm.>] [We have been importer of {shoes<请填写本次贸易涉及的货物>} for many years.|< We are in the line of {shoes<请填写本次贸易涉及的货物>}.>|<{shoes<请填写本次贸易涉及的货物>} fall within our business activities.>] At present, we are interested in extending our range and [would appreciate your catalogues and quotations.|< would you please send us your full-range catalogue with price list for our consideration?>] [If your prices are competitive we would expect to transact a significant volume of business.|< If your products are satisfactory and prices right, we expect to place regular orders for large numbers >|< Provided your price is found competitive and delivery date acceptable, we intend to place a large order with you.>] <br>\n[We look forward to your early reply.|< We trust you will give us an early reply.>|< We look forward to receiving the above information at your earliest convenience. >]<br>\n                                                             Very truly yours，<br> \n', '', '', '自米兰厄里斯托鞋类公司取得贵公司和地址，特此修函，祈能发展关系。多年来，本公司经营鞋类进口生意，现欲扩展业务范围，盼能惠赐商品目录和报价表。 如价格公道，本公司必大额订购。 烦请早日赐复。 此致<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('27', '购货商看到广告后去函索要价目表', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[We are interested in increasing our range of {car heaters<请填写我方经营产品种类>} and|< Seeing your advertisement of car heaters<请填写我方经营产品种类>} and we>|< We find that your car heaters<请填写我方经营产品种类>} are popular in our market and>] should like to [receive information about|< learn more about|< know the details of>] {the various models<请填写对方生产的产品>} [you are at present producing.|< provided now>|< which are available now>]<br>\nWe should be [obliged|< appreciated >|< grateful>] if you would send us your {latest catalogue and price list, together with details of the CX4 heater advertised in the current issue of the MOTORING MONTHLY.< 请填写希望对方提供的相关材料>}<br>\n                                                         Yours very truly, <br>\n', '', '', '我方有兴趣增加汽车散热器销售的种类，希望获得贵方目前正在生产各种散热器型号的信息。<br>\n如果贵方能将最新的产品目录、价目表并连同最近在《汽车月刊》上刊登广告的CX4型散热器的详细信息发给我方，我方将会及时做出回应。<br>\n此致<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('28', '进口商接出口商来电函后询价', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[Thank you for your letter dated|< We have received your letter of>|< We welcome your letter dated>] {October 15,< 请填写对方来函时间>} [informing us of the details of your {new kitchen ventilators<请填写对方来函中介绍的信息>}.|< giving the details of your {new kitchen ventilators<请填写对方来函中介绍的信息>} to us.>|< introducing us the details of your {new kitchen ventilators<请填写对方来函中介绍的信息>}.>] [We find there is an increasing demand for the {reversible type of ventilator.< 请填写我方所感兴趣的产品>}|< Every sign of {reversible type of ventilator.< 请填写我方所感兴趣的产品>}    market shows a tendency to improve.>|< The prices of {reversible type of ventilator.< 请填写我方所感兴趣的产品>} are expected to go up within the next few months.>] <br>\nWe would like to receive details of {your reversible ventilators, together with prices and the terms.< 请填写希望对方提供的材料>} [We look forward to receiving the above information at your earliest convenience.|< We look forward to hearing from you soon.>|< We hope to receive your reply at an early date.>] <br>\n                                                            Yours faithfully, <br>\n', '', '', '感谢贵方10月15日来函，向我方介绍新款厨房通风设备的详细信息。经我方市场调研发现，对循环式通风设备的需求不断上升。<br>\n我方期盼获得贵方生产的循环式通风设备的详细信息及价格和其他销售条件。敬盼贵方方便时给予回复。此致<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('29', '进口商询价并要求最优惠条件', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[We are in the market for {Vinyl Sandals<请填写我方所经营的行业>} of your manufacture|< We understand that you are a manufacturer of {Vinyl Sandals<请填写我方所经营的行业>}>|< We are in the line of {Vinyl Sandals<请填写我方所经营的行业>} of your manufacture>] and shall be glad if you will send us {a copy of your illustrated catalogue<请填写希望对方提供的材料>}, [informing us of your best terms and lowest prices {CIF Singapore.< 请填写希望对方提供的材料>}|< being interested to know your latest quotations for {CIF Singapore.< 请填写希望对方提供的材料>}>|< making us an offer with prices {CIF Singapore.< 请填写希望对方提供的材料>} for above items>] [As we are in a position to handle large quantities, we trust that you will make an effort to submit an offer on your most advantageous terms.|< If your products are satisfactory and prices right, we expect to place regular orders for large numbers >|< We should be glad if you would send us a copy of your catalogue and any other information that may help us to make the best choice of easy sale products.>] [We are looking forward to your soon reply.|< We await your early reply.>|< Your early reply is highly appreciated.>] <br>\n                                                        Faithfully yours, <br>\n', '', '', '我公司一直从事精塑凉鞋的销售，得知贵方进行此类产品生产，希望能获得一份附插图的产品目录，并告知我方贵方的最优惠条件及新加坡最低到岸价格。如贵方能提供最大的优惠，我方必有大额订单。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('30', '进口商询价并要求寄送样品', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[Please send us the catalogue and samples of {your silk cushions<请填写我方希望进口的商品\n>} advertised in {the third issue of China Pictorial, Overseas Edition of last March.< 请填写获知信息的来源>}|< We have learned your name and address from{the third issue of China Pictorial, Overseas Edition of last March.< 请填写获知信息的来源>}, and shall be pleased if you send us the catalogue and samples of {your silk cushions<请填写我方希望进口的商品>}.>|< We have your information from {the third issue of China Pictorial, Overseas Edition of last March.< 请填写获知信息的来源>} and will be glad to receive from you by airmail catalogue and samples of {your silk cushions<请填写我方希望进口的商品>}.>]<br>\nAs you may know, we have imported these lines of goods from your country in [large quantities|< large number>|< large amount>] [{during the past five years<请填写我方已从事此类产品贸易的时间>}|< in these years>|< during these years>], and [we should be very much obliged if you would send us samples of good and medium qualities which you can supply from stock.|< we would like to received samples of good and medium qualities which you can supply from stock.>|< would you pleased to send samples of good and medium qualities which you can supply from stock?>] <br>\n[If you give us a really competitive quotation, we may place a substantial order.|< If your products are satisfactory and prices right, we expect to place regular orders for large numbers >|< As we are in a position to handle large quantities, we trust that you will make an effort to submit an offer on your most advantageous terms.>] <br>\n                                                         Yours faithfully, <br>\n', '', '', '贵方在今年第三期《中国画报》海外版第三版中发布了丝绸垫子的广告，我方期望能获得产品的目录及样品。<br>\n正如贵方所知，近五年来我方从贵国进口了大量此类产品。如果贵方向我方提供品质良好的产品样本，我方必将及时反馈相关信息。<br>\n如贵方能提供一个有竞争力的报价，我方必有大笔订单。<br>\n    此致<br>\n敬礼<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('31', '询价并咨询是否可寄样', '', '', 'Dear Sirs: <br>\n     [We learn from|< We have your information from>|< We have your name and address from>]{**company/ ** dated XXX<请填写获得信息的来源>} that [you are producing for export {hand-made shoes in **materials.< 请填写欲进口的商品>}|< you are in the line of {hand-made shoes in **materials.< 请填写欲进口的商品>}>|<{hand-made shoes in **materials.<请填写欲进口的商品>} fall within your business activities.>] [There is a steady demand here for high-class goods of this type. |< The prices of goods are expected to go up within the next few months.>|<As the supply position at this end is extremely tight, the present market is undoubtedly a seller’s marke>]A good price and sales can be obtained for this [design.|< model>|< style>]<br>\n     [Will you please send us your {catalog and full details of your export prices and terms of payment<请填写希望对方提供的相关材料>}?|< We shall be grateful if you could send us {catalog and full details of your export prices and terms of payment<请填写希望对方提供的相关材料>}.>|< We would like to received your {catalog and full details of your export prices and terms of payment<请填写希望对方提供的相关材料>}.>]<br>\n     [We look forward to hearing from you soon. |<Your early reply will be appreciated.>|< Your early quotation will be highly appreciated >]<br>\n                                                             Yours faithfully, <br>\n', '', '', '我方从XX公司X月X日来函获悉，贵方制作XX材料手工鞋以供出口。我国对此类高质量产品有稳定需求。这种设计定能售出不错的价格，获得很好的销量。<br>\n贵方能否将产品目录寄予我方，附上出口价格详细信息及付款方式。<br>\n期待贵方早日恢复。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('32', '报价并建议支付方式', '', '', 'Dir Sirs：<br>\n[Thank you for your letter of {the 16th of this month.<请填写上封函电的日期，便于对方掌握函电所涉事项>}|< Your inquiry of {the 16th of this month.<请填写上封函电的日期，便于对方掌握函电所涉事项>} is greatly appreciated.>|< We have received your inquiry of {the 16th of this month.<请填写上封函电的日期，便于对方掌握函电所涉事项>}.>] [We shall be glad to enter into business relations with your company.|< We are desire of establishing direct relations with you.>|< We also hope to build trade relationship with your company.>] [In compliance with|< According to>|< On the basis of>] your request, we are sending you, {under separate cover, our latest catalogue and price list covering our export range.<请填写随函附寄的资料>} [Payment should be made by {irrevocable and confirmed letter of credit.<请填写期望的支付方式，如信用证、汇付、托收等>}|< We hope you can accept the payment term of {irrevocable and confirmed letter of credit.<请填写期望的支付方式，如信用证、汇付、托收等>}.>|< Our usual payment is {irrevocable and confirmed letter of credit.<请填写期望的支付方式，如信用证、汇付、托收等>}.>] [Should you wish to place an order, please telex or fax us.|< Your early quotation will be highly appreciated.>|< Looking forward to your early order.>] <br>\n                                                         Yours truly，<br>\n', '', '', '本月16日收到有关商务关系的来函，不胜欣喜。谨遵要求另函奉上最新之出口商品目录和报价单。款项烦请以不可撤销保兑之信用证支付。如欲订货，请电传或传真为盼。<br>\n    此致 <br>\n敬礼<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('33', '应要求寄产品目录及价目表', '', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n   [We thank you for your letter of {17th January,< 请填写收到来函时间>}|< Your inquiry of {17th January,< 请填写收到来函时间>} is greatly appreciated.>|< We have received your inquiry of {17th January,< 请填写收到来函时间>}.>] [asking for details and prices of|< wishing to have the information of>|< being interested in>] {our car heaters.< 请填写对方来函中询问的产品名称>}<br>\n[We have pleasure in enclosing our {latest price list and catalogue, together with details of Model CX4. <请填写我方将提供的资料>}|< We are pleased to send you our{latest price list and catalogue, together with details of Model CX4. <请填写我方将提供的资料>}>|<{latest price list and catalogue, together with details of Model CX4. <请填写我方将提供的资料>} will be airmailed to you as soon as possible.>] <br>\n\n', '', '', '感谢贵方1月17日来信询问我公司汽车散热器的详细信息和价格。<br>\n我方随信附寄最新的价目表及产品目录，以及CX4型散热器的相关参数信息。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('34', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('35', '报价并对及时装运做出保证', '', '', 'Dear Sir, <br>\n[Thank you for your inquiry of|< We have received your letter of>|< Thank you for your letter of>] {September 3.< 请填写收到来函的时间>} [We hasten to send you|< Under separate cover, we are sending you>|< To comply with your request, we are sending you herewith >] {our complete catalogue, in which you will find a full description of our entire line of goods.<>} <br>\nOn the enclosed price list you will note {our rock-bottom quotation CIF Singapore. <请填写我方提供的价格>} [We can promise delivery in|<The shipment will be made in >] {five weeks<请填写运输所需时间>} if we receive your order [immediately.|< in these two months>|< before June>] [Please cable us on receipt of this letter.|< Your prompt reply will be appreciated!>|< We are anticipating your answer.>] <br>\n                                                         Yours faithfully,\n\n', '', '', '感谢贵方9月3日来函。我方急切向贵方寄发我公司全部产品的目录，包含产品详细描述。<br>\n随信附上产品价目表，显示了我公司新加坡最低到岸价格。我方保证在接到贵方合约五周内将产品运到。望贵方收到信件后与我方电话联系。<br>\n    此致<br>\n敬礼<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('36', '回函同意寄样并报价', '18813192817@163.com', '', 'Dear Sirs, <br>\n[In reply to your inquiry dated|< We have received your letter of>|< Thank you for your letter of>] {May 22,< 请填写对方来函时间>} we are [sending|< mailing >] you [patterns|<styles>|< models >] of our {newly finished printed silk,<请填写我方欲寄样品名称>} and [have pleasure|< pleas[ed>|< glad>] in quoting you as follows: <br>\n{Item No.110, two colors, U.S.$ 1.5 per pce. <br>\nItem No.111, three colors, U.S.$ 1.8 per pce. <br>\n…<请填写样品详细列表>}<br>\n{CIF your port including your commission 2%.<请填写价格方式及佣金>}<br>\n[Your early reply will be appreciated.|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.\n>|< We are anticipating your answer.>] <br>\n                                                       Faithfully yours, <br>\n', '', '18813192817@163.com', '\n回复贵方5月22日的来函，寄予贵方我公司新款丝绸样品，详列如下：<br>\n110号产品，两种颜色，每件1.5美元。<br>\n111号产品，三种颜色，每件1.8美元。<br>\n……<br>\n到你方港口价格，包含2%的佣金。<br>\n期盼贵方早日回复。<br>\n    此致<br>\n敬礼<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('37', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('38', '发盘同时推荐其它产品', '', '', '\nDear Mr. Jones:<br>We thank you for your letter dated {April 8<请填写对方来函时间>}inquiring about our{leather handbags.<请填写对方询问的产品>}[As requested|<In response to your enquiry,>][we take pleasure in offering you|<we are pleased to send you our quotation|We are pleased to send you our offer|we are pleased to quote as follows>],subject to our final confirmation,{300 dozen deerskin handbags<请填写我方发盘的数量>}style{No.MS190<请填写我方发盘的型号、款式>}at{$124.00 per dozen<请填写我方发盘的价格>}{CIF Hamburg<请填写产品价格类型>}.[Shipment will be effected|<Shipment to be made>]within{20 days<请填写发货期限>}after{receipt of the relevant L/C issued by your first class bank in our favor upon signing Sales Contract<请填写我方发货条件>}.<br>We are manufacturing various kinds of\n{leather purses and waist belts<请填写我方欲推荐的产品>}for export,[and enclos a brochure of products for your reference|<and we are enclosing our quotation for your reference|and send catalogue enabling you to make suitable selection>].We hope some of them meet your taste and needs.<br>[If we can be of any further help|<If any further help needed>],please feel free to let us know. Customers\' inquiries are always meet with our careful attention.<br>[We are looking forward to your early order.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>[Sincerely,|<Best regards,|Yours truly,|Faithfully yours,>]<br>', null, null, '尊敬的琼斯先生：<br>感谢贵方4月8日来函询问我方生产的皮制手提包相关信息。按贵方要求，我方十分乐意向贵方发盘进行最后确认，300打MS190款鹿皮手提包，每打汉堡到岸价格为124美元。我方将在收到贵方信用证开证行根据双方签署的销售合同开出的信用证相关凭证20日内装船发货。<br>同时，我公司还生产多种供出口的皮制钱包和皮带，随函附上产品手册以供贵方参考。希望其中有适合贵方需要的产品。<br>如果我方能提供其他任何帮助，请随时与我方联系。我方对客户的要求必将给予认真回应。<br>谨上<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('39', '卖方根据购货询函报出实盘', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>[Thank you very much for your inquiry of|<Thank you for your interest in our commodity in your letter of|We are in receipt of your letter of|It delighted us very much to receive a letter from you dated>]{June 6, 2008<请填写受到对方来函时间>}.[We take great pleasure in quoting|<we are pleased to send you our quotation|we are pleased to send you our offer|we are pleased to quote>] as follows:<br>ITEM:{******<请填写产品名称>}<br>SPECIFICATIONS:{******<请填写产品规格>}<br>QUANTITY:{******<请填写欲售产品数量>}<br>PRICE:{******<请填写产品价格>}<br>DELIVERY:{******<请填写欲采取的运输方式>}<br>PAYMENT:{******<请填写付款方式>}<br>VALIDITY:{******<请填写发盘的有效期>}<br>We hope that this will meet with[your requirements|<your taste and needs>].[We are looking forward to your early order.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>[Faithfully yours|<Best regards|Yours truly|Sincerely].<br>', '', '', '敬启者：<br>感谢受到贵方2008年6月6日来函。我方十分荣幸地向您介绍如下产品：<br>品名：******<br>规格：******<br>数量：******<br>价格：******<br>运输方式：******<br>付款方式：******<br>有效期：******<br>希望以上条件满足贵方要求。<br>盼复。<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('40', '卖方根据询价对外报盘，并规定最低起订数量', '', '', '\nDear Sirs,<br>[Thank you for your letter dated|<Thank you very much for your inquiry of|We are in receipt of your letter of|It delighted us very much to receive a letter from you dated>]{Mar. 22<请填写对方来函时间>}.[As you requested|<In response to your enquiry>]we hereby airmail by separate mail{one copy of the catalogue of our printed cotton cloth<请填写我方提供的相关材料>}.<br>In order to start business between us, we are making you the following favorable offer, subject to a minimum order of{15, 000 YD<请填写最低起订数量>}.<br>{Article:<br>Color:<br>Specification:<请填写品名及规格>}<br>Quantity:{ <请填写欲售数量>}<br>Packing:{ <请填写欲采用的包装方式>}<br>Price:{ <请填写价格>}<br>Shipment:{ <请填写运输方式>}<br>Payment:{ <请填写付款方式>}<br>[We are hoping that the above conditions will be of acceptance to you|<We hope that this will meet with your requirements>], and[looking forward to your trial order|<We hope that this will meet with your requirements>],and[looking forward to your trial order.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>[Faithfully yours<Best regards|Yours truly|Sincerely>],<br>\n', null, null, '敬启者：<br>感谢贵方3月22日来函。按贵方要求，我方以航空邮件向贵方寄发一份棉布的产品目录。<br>为了双方间开展贸易，我方向贵方提供如下优惠的发盘，最低起订数量为15，000码。<br>品名：<br>颜色：<br>规格：<br>数量：<br>包装方式：<br>价格：<br>运输方式：<br>付款方式：<br>希望贵方接受以上条款并期待贵方试定。<br>谨上<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('41', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('42', '市场因素', '', '', 'Dear Sir,<br>[In reference to your E-mail|<Thank you for your letter of|We are in receipt of your letter of|It delighted us very much to receive a letter from you dated>]of{August 1<请填写对方来函时间>},[we cannot make a better offer than the one we suggested to you|<we regret that we cannot accept your counter offer or even meet you half way|we cannot entertain your counteroffer>],we feel that offer itself is most generous[under the circumstances|<up to the present market level|in keeping with the current rate>].<br>In checking our books, we find that you have purchased from us {twice as much the first three months of this year as you did in the first three months of last year<请填写我方拒绝还盘的理由，如对方今年同期订货增加>}. This indicates to us that you have been successful in retailing our merchandise.<br>We hope that upon reconsideration you will be able to accept our offer. We have been very pleased to[have you on our list of accounts|<wait for your trial order>].<br>[We are anticipating your early reply.|<We are looking forward to your early reply!|We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>[Sincerely|<Best regards|Yours truly|Yours faithfully>],<br>xxx<br>\n\n\n\n\n', null, null, '敬启者：<br>关于你方8月1日来函所谈价格事宜，我们的报价已经是当前经济情况下最优惠的，不能再低了。<br>经查对账目发现，贵方今年的头3个月在我处所购的货物是去年同期的两倍。说明我们的货物很畅销。<br>因此希望贵方重新考虑，并接受我们的最初报价。如能达成此次交易，我们不胜荣幸。<br>谨上，<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('43', '竞争对手反应', '', '', 'Dear Sir,<br>We[have been very pleased with|<are very interested in|are interested to handle|have interest in|take interest in>]your product, as you know. However, we find that[we can obtain a price of|<the price is too high to be acceptable which is|the price is too high to accept which is|the price is too high to be accepted which is>]{$4.00 per hundred<请填写我方获得的低报价>}with a local firm. This is{fifty cents per hundred<请填写我方获得的新报价比对方低的数量>}lower than your price.<br>[If you can see your way clear to meet these figures,|<We would suggest that you reconsider your price and send us a suitable quotation. If you consider our counter-offer most favorably,|Since products of equal quality can be bought easily elsewhere at lower prices，we sincerely hope that you will consider our counter-offer most favorably, and>]we would be pleased to place with you an order that will carry us{for the rest of this year<请填写我方将在何时与对方按新价格签订合同>}.That order is likely to be one of the largest that we have ever placed with you.<br>[We are anticipating your early reply.|<We are looking forward to your early reply!|We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>[Sincerely,|<Best regards.|Yours truly,|Yours faithfully,>]<br>', null, null, '敬启者：<br>正如您所了解的，我们对贵公司的产品一向很满意。然而，一家本地公司报价仅4美元/百件，比贵公司价格低50美分。<br>如果你方也能提供这样的价格，我们年底前愿意就此下一笔订单。该项订单有可能会是双方合作过最大的一笔。<br>谨上，<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('44', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('45', '尚有存货', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>[We are in receipt of your letter of|<We acknowledge receipt of your letter of|Thank you for your letter of|It delighted us very much to receive a letter from you dated>]{22 March<请填写对方来函时间>},offering us the residue stock of{MOTORMAN repair kits<请填写对方发盘销售的产品>}.<br>We have checked our own stocks of{similar kits<请填写我方库存的类似产品>}.Nevertheless,[if you are prepared to increase your discount to|<if you can offer a discount of>]{25%<请填写我方希望对方提供的折扣率>} for the complete stock, so that we in turn can make a special offer to our customers, then[we are willing to buy|<we are willing to make an order>].<br>[We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|<We are looking forward to your early reply!|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>[Yours faithfully,|<Best Regards,|Yours truly,|Sincerely,>]<br>\n\n\n', null, null, '敬启者：<br>我方收到贵方3月22日来函，向我方发盘以销售贵方库存的汽车维修工具包。<br>经检查库存发现，我方类似产品仍有很高库存量，特别是卡曼型维修包和快速维修包。<br>然而，如果贵方将这批产品的折扣提高到25%，我方可以向客户进行特别发盘，那么我方将购买这批货物。<br>谨上<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('46', '长期贸易关系', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>[With reference to your offer|<In reply>],[we regret to tell you that|<we very much regret to state that>]{your price is on<请填写拒绝发盘的原因>}the high side.[Considering|<In view of>][the long term cooperation between us|<our long-standing business relationship>],could you kindly[reduce a little to make the price as|<reduce a price to|reduce a price by|bring down to>]{USD475?<请填写希望对方提供的价格>}We are waiting for your good news.<br>[Your early reply will be highly appreciated.|<We are looking forward your early reply!|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.|We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.>]<br>[Yours faithfully|<Best Regards|Yours truly|Sincerely>],<br>\n\n\n', null, null, '敬启者：<br>关于贵方的发盘，很遗憾地通知您我方认为贵方价格过高。考虑到双方长期的合作关系，恳请贵方将价格下调至475美元，可否？期盼贵方尽早给予有利的回复。<br>谨上<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('47', '同类商品存货较足，如能降价则考虑购买', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>We are in receipt of your letter of{22 March<请填写对方来函时间>},offering us the residue stock of{MOTORMAN repair kits<请填写对方发盘销售的产品>}.<br>We have checked our own stocks of{similar kits<请填写我方库存的类似产品>}and find that they are quite high, in particular{KARMAN kits and MEND-IT-QUICK kits<请填写上一空中所提产品的型号>}.Nevertheless, if you are prepared to increase your discount to{25%<请填写我方希望对方提供的折扣率>}for the complete stock, so that we in turn can make a special offer to our customers, then we are willing to buy.<br>', null, null, '敬启者：<br>我方收到贵方3月22日来函，向我方发盘以销售贵方库存的汽车维修工具包。<br>经检查库存发现，我方类似产品仍有很高库存量，特别是卡曼型维修包和快速维修包。然而，如果贵方将这批产品的折扣提高到25%，我方可以向客户进行特别发盘，那么我方将购买这批货物。<br>谨上<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('48', '卖方难以接受订单并致歉', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>[It was a pleasure to receive the sizable order|<We acknowledge receipt of your order|Thank you for your order|It delighted us very much to receive such a good order from you>]for{Viny1 Raincoats<请填写对方欲购产品>}which you were good enough to place with us. However,[we regret to inform you that|<we are sorry to inform you that|we regret having to disappoint you because|we regret having to cause you disappointment because>]{the late demand had been so great that the manufactures, who usually keep a big reserve stock<请填写无法接受对方订单的原因，如库存不足>}left,[and we are not certain when we can expect delivery|<and cannot meet your requirements for the moment>].[Under these circumstances, we regret our inability to serve you at the moment.|<Although we cannot meet your requirements for the moment，please be assured that whenever the situation changes favorably，we will contact you without failure.|Our inability to accept your order in question is only a temporary phenomenon.  As soon as the supply situation is cleared up,we shall contact you with the least possible delay.|\nYou must be aware that it is the last thing we would do to decline an order from our old clients.| Since the situation gives us no other choice，We hope you will show understanding.>]<br> Yours truly,<br>', null, null, '敬启者：<br>十分感谢贵方给予我方数量可观的维尼1型雨衣订单。但是，很遗憾地通知贵方，虽然生产厂家以往一直保持大量库存，由于近期需求激增，维尼1型雨衣已无库存，我方不能肯定何时能给贵方发货。基于上述原因，我方暂时无法与贵方签订合同。<br>谨上<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('49', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('50', '接受订单并希望保持长期业务关系', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>[It delighted us very much to receive such a good order from you|<We acknowledge receipt of your offer of|It was a pleasure to receive the sizable order|Thank you for your order>](after a lapse of time which had been regrettably long).<br>[Our factory has been instructed to start manufacture at once|<We are glad to inform you that the goods on your order are suppliable for prompt delivery|The goods in question are unavailable for the moment，but are suppliable for deferred delivery|We have checked our own stocks and find that they are quite high>], and the goods will be shipped on board {the “Ganges”<请填写承运货船名称>}which is [scheduled to|<due to|intended to>][sail from|<depart from>]{Kobe<请填写起运港名称>}on or about the{May 21<请填写预计起运日期>}.We hope this order will be followed by many more.<br>We have always [appreciated|<been grateful for>]our friendly relations with your firm and shall do our best to [maintain them|<further our cooperation>].<br>Truly yours,<br>', null, null, '敬启者：<br>十分高兴获得贵方的大订单（即使是在有些令人遗憾的长期等待之后）。<br>接到订单我方工厂立即投入生产，预计将在5月21日左右由恒河号货轮从神户港装运起航。期盼此次合作成功为今后进一步贸易创造条件。<br>我方十分珍视与贵公司的友好合作关系，将尽最大努力保持双方关系良好的发展势头。<br>谨上<br>\n');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('51', '同意付款交单', '', '', 'You are [aware|<informed>]that[{L/C<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>} payment is our usual practice|<payment by _is rather more practice to us.>][Regarding the business in question|<In view of your being our old customer|In order to expand mutual business>],it was only in consideration of[our good relationship |<our cooperative relationship>]that[we give you an accommodation by agreeing to{D/P<请填写我方同意更改的付款条件>} instead of {L/C<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>}|<we can change payment terms from {L/C<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>} to {D/P<请填写我方同意更改的付款条件>}|we can take flexible ways in adopting {D/P<请填写我方同意更改的付款条件>} payment terms instead of {L/C<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>}>].<br> \n\n\n\n\n', null, null, ' 贵方应该注意到信用证是我方通常使用的付款方式。考虑到双方良好的商业关系，我方为了给予贵方便利，同意以付款交单代替信用证方式付款。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('52', '选择托收付款方式', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,<br>[Thank you for your order of|<It delighted us very much to receive such a good order from you|We acknowledge receipt of your offer of|It was a pleasure to receive the sizable order>]{July 5th<请填写对方来函时间>}(Order{No.12345<请填写对方订单号>}).[I am pleased to inform you that|<I am pleased to inform you that >]we have completed your order and is sending it today{by fax<请填写通信方式>} to{your address<请填写通信方式>}.<br>[As agreed|<In reference to our agreement>] we have forwarded our bill{No. 123 <请填写单据号>}for {$10,000<请填写单据金额>}with the documents to your bank, Beijing branch of China Bank. The draft has been made out for payment{10 days<请填写见票后几日付款>} after sight, and the documents will be handed to you on acceptance.<br> \n[Yours faithfully,|<Best Regards,|Yours truly,|Sincerely,]<br>', null, null, '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('53', '选择货到付款交单', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,[Thank you for your reply to our offer in your last letter of|<We acknowledge receipt of your letter of|Thank you for your letter of|It delighted us very much to receive a letter from you|We are in receipt of your letter of|We have duly received your letter of>]{June 5th<请填写对方来函时间>}. Under the present[system of payment|<payment conditions|payment terms>]{by D/P at sight<请填写对方提出的付款条件>},the consignment has to be paid long before its arrival. Therefore, [we hope you will accommodate us by accepting|<it would help us greatly if you would accept|would you like to take flexible ways in adopting>]{payment against documents<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>}upon arrival of the goods. If you agree with us in the payment term, we will send you the final sale contract to proceed this business.<br>[We are looking forward to your early reply.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.|Your kindly reply will be appreciated.>]<br>[Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards,|Yours truly,|Yours faithfully,>]<br>\n\n\n\n\n', null, null, '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('54', '建议将信用证方式改为跟单托收', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,[We have duly received your letter of|<We acknowledge receipt of your letter of|Thank you for your letter of|It delighted us very much to receive a letter from you|We are in receipt of your letter of|Thank you for your reply to our offer in your last letter of>]{June 10th<请填写对方来函时间>}and thank you for your offering a firm offer to us.[As in most cases we have to pay a deposit to the bank when opening {L/C<请填写对方要求的付款条件>}, payment by {L/C<请填写对方要求的付款条件>} is rather more expensive to us.|<would you like to reconsider your payment conditions\nyou have to take flexible ways in adopting payment terms.|We hope you will accommodate its in this respect, and let us have a revised quotation.|It would help us greatly if you would accept D/P.|We hope you will accommodate us by accepting payment against documents upon arrival of the goods.>]To make a long-standing business relationship between us,[would you like to change payment terms from L/C to documentary collection?|<would you like to reconsider your payment conditions?|you have to take flexible ways in adopting payment terms.|we hope you will accommodate its in this respect, and let us have a revised quotation|it would help us greatly if you would accept D/P.|we hope you will accommodate us by accepting payment against documents upon arrival of the goods.>][Your kindly reply will be appreciated.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.|We are looking forward to your early reply!>]<br>[Yours,|<Best Regards,|Yours truly,|\nYours faithfully,>]<br>\n\n\n\n\n', null, null, '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('55', '建议采用D/P方式', '', '', 'Dear Sirs,[We have pleasure in advising you|<We are pleased to have you known|We are pleased to inform you>]that your offer of{October 16th<请填写对方来函时间>}has been accepted. As the amount involved for this transaction is below{$1,000.00<请填写金额>},[we hope that you will agree to|<it would help us greatly if you would accept|would you like to take flexible ways in adopting>]{D/P<请填写我方希望的付款条件>}payment terms. If we could reach agreement in this matter,[we will place a larger order next time.|<this order will be followed by many more in the future.|repeat orders will be possibly placed before long.>]<br>[An early reply would be appreciated as we wish to reach a prompt decision.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.|We are looking forward to your early reply!>]<br>[Yours,|<Best Regards,|Yours truly,|Yours faithfully,>]<br>\n\n\n\n\n', null, null, '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('56', '修改托收内容——卖方致函买方，不同意对方提出的货款托收条件 ', '', '', 'A seller is writing to his buyer, declining the newly proposed terms of payment on collection<br>Re: “Toshiba” brand Refrigerator<br>[We receive with thanks for your |<Thank you for your|We are in receipt of your|It delighted us very much to receive your>]fax dated{Sept. 15, 2008<请填写对方来函时间>}and appreciate your intention to push the sales of our refrigerators in your area.<br>[We regret that we are unable to accept your request for payment on {D/A (Documents against Acceptance) terms<请填写对方提出的付款条件>}-usually we ask for {payment by L/C.<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>}|<In reply, we regret our being unable to grant your payment on {D/A (Documents against Acceptance) terms<请填写对方提出的付款条件>}, as it is our usual practice to ask for sight {payment by L/C.<请填写我方通常要求的付款条件>}.>]<br>But[in view of|<regarding|considering>]the small quantity involved and[the friendly relations between us, ⑸we will, as an exception, accept|<long friendly business relations between us|long years of satisfactory trading>]payment for your trial order on{D/P (Documents against Payment)<请填写同意对方何种付款条件>}basis. In other words, we will draw on you by documentary draft at sight, through our bank, on collection basis, without{L/C<请填写对方不再需要提交的材料>}.<br>We hope the above[payment terms|<payment conditions>]will be acceptable to you and expect to receive your trial order in due course.<br>[We look forward to your early reply.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.>]<br>\n\n\n\n\n', null, null, '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('57', '催促付款——通知对方办理付款 ', '', '', 'Asking your customer to make payment<br>Dear Mr. Mark,<br>[We have pleasure in advising you that|<we are glad to have you known that|we are pleased to inform you that>]your order of{October 16 <请填写对方下订单时间>}has been shipped today per{s.s. “Calches”<请填写承运船名称>} from{Veracruz<请填写启运港名称>}.<br>Enclosed you may find our invoice{No. 12345 for U.S.D.25,000<请填写发票号及金额>}and please note that we have drawn on you for this amount at{45 days<请填写希望对方付款的期限>}attaching the shipping documents to our draft.<br>[As arranged|<According to arrangement>],we have instructed our bank to give up the documents against payment of our draft which we recommend to your protection.<br>[We look forward to your early reply.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.|Your early reply is appreciated.|We are anticipating your answer.|Your prompt reply will be appreciated!>]<br>[Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards,|Yours truly,|Yours faithfully,>]<br>\n\n\n', null, null, '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('58', '要求暂缓付款 Defer a payment', '', '', 'SUNSHINE FLAVOURS LTD<br>\n23 Emerald Drive, Shannon Technology Park,<br>\nCork CO5 35TS, Republic of Ireland<br>\nMme Susanne Dufrais,<br>\nLee Gourmets Du Poitou S.A.<br>\n45, Rue Mirabeau,<br>\n23000 Poitiers, France<br>\n                                                         3 Sept, 2008<br>\nDear Sirs,<br>\nAs you will remember from our telephone call, we {have recently been experiencing a number of difficulties with several large customers. <请填写我方目前存在的困难>} This [has resulted in|<has led to>|<has brought about>|<has caused>] {unfortunate delays in paying outstanding accounts.<请填写由于上述困难造成的问题>ŽఀԀ㜀\0\0\0\0\0are very sorry|<We regret>]  that your company has been affected by these developments.<br> [We are doing everything possible to rectify the situation.|<Anything possible to improve the situation has being done.>] Indeed we hope to be able to settle our debts within the very near future.<br> [We would very much appreciate it|<It would be appreciated>|<We shall be grateful>] if you could bear with us patiently. As we are sure that liquidation on our part would not be in your interest either.<br>[Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards>|<Yours truly>|<Yours faithfully,>]<br>William Berker<br>', '', '', '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('59', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('60', '催证并提醒对方注意与合同条款保持一致\nUrging the L/C and emphasizing its conformity with the clauses of S/C', '', '', '[With reference to|<Concerning>] {the 200 dozen blouses<请填写欲销售的产品名称、数量>} under our sales confirmation {No.12345<请填写销售确认书编号>}, we wish to draw your attention to the fact that the date of shipment is approaching, but[we still have not received your covering {L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>} to date|<{L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>}has not come to hand>|<{L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>} fail to appear>|<{L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>}fail to reach us>|<up to the time of writing, we have not received {L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>}>|<up to the present writing，we have not yet received {L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>}>]. Please do your best to [establish|<open>|<issue>] your ③L/C so that we can execute your order in time.<br> [In order to|<For the sake of>] avoid subsequent amendments, please see to it that the ③L/C stipulations are in exact accordance with {the terms of the contract.<请填写希望上述单证与之对应的文件名称>}<br> [We hope to receive your favorable news soon.|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.>|<Your early reply is appreciated.>|<We are anticipating your answer.>|<Your prompt reply will be appreciated!>]<br> [Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards>|<Yours truly>|<Yours faithfully,>]<br>', '', '', '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('61', '催促迟迟不到的信用证 \nUrging a belated L/C', '', '', 'We have cabled you on the {12, 15 and 19 of May<请填写双方联系的多次时间>}, asking you to [establish|<open>|<issue>] your covering {L/C<请填写对方未给我方的单证名称>} under our Sales Contract {No.12345<请填写合同号>}.[But so far we have not received any of your reply.|<Up to the time of writing, we have not received any of your reply.>|<Up to the time of writing, we have not received any of your reply.>]<br> We want to remind you that you promised to open your relevant L/C upon receipt of our confirmation. But {two months<请填写对方单证已经迟到的时间长度>} have passed before  [we can receive any news from you|<any news comes to hand>|<any news appears>|<any news reaches us>].We have prepared the goods {one month|<请填写我方货物已备齐的时间长度>} ago, and we can not find any reason on your part [to postpone the establishment of your L/C|<for delay of L/C>|<for delay in opening L/C>|<for failure to establish L/C>].Please try to establish your L/C as soon as possible. Otherwise you will have to {bear the additional storing charges|<请填写如果对方单证仍不寄到的后果>}. <br> [Your prompt reply will be appreciated!|<We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date.>|<Your early reply is appreciated.>|<We are anticipating your answer.>]<br> [Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards>|<Yours truly>|<Yours faithfully,>]<br>', '', '', '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('62', '通知信用证已到——通知对方信用证已经收到\nAcknowledge the receipt of L/C ', '', '', 'We have just been informed by {the National Bank of New York, Shanghai<请填写我方开户行名称>}, [that they received through their head office of your city {an irrevocable letter of credit<请填写收到的单证名称>} opened by you,|<that your {irrevocable letter of credit<请填写收到的单证名称>} arrived>|<your {irrevocable letter of credit<请填写收到的单证名称>} reached us>|<of arrival of your {irrevocable letter of credit<请填写收到的单证名称>}>] {No.12345<请填写单证编号>} to cover your order {No.133<请填写合同编号>}.<br> [We are going to ship the goods by {the NK M/S ”Dongfeng”<请填写承运货船名称>} sailing from {Shanghai<请填写启运港>} on {the 23 of this month<请填写启运时间>}.|<We can effect shipment by {the NK M/S ”Dongfeng”<请填写承运货船名称>}sailing from {Shanghai<请填写启运港>}on {the 23 of this month<请填写启运时间>}.>|<the ship sailing for your port is {the NK M/S ”Dongfeng”<请填写承运货船名称>}scheduled to leave {Shanghai<请填写启运港>}on or about {the 23 of this month<请填写启运时间>}.>|<The cargo will be shipped by {the NK M/S ”Dongfeng”<请填写承运货船名称>}from {Shanghai<请填写启运港>}on {the 23 of this month<请填写启运时间>}.>]<br> [Thank you for your prompt arrangement for the L/C.|<Thank you for your prompt arrangement for the L/C, and hope more order in the future.>]<br> [Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards>|<Yours truly>|<Yours faithfully,>]<br>', '', '', '无');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('63', '贸促会', '', '', '\"Dear Sirs,<br>\n[We have heard from|< We learn from>|< Having your name and address through >|< We are writing to you at the suggestion of >] {China Council for the Promotion of International Trade<请填写获知信息的来源>} that you are [in the market for|< in the line of >|< specializing in>] {electric appliances<请填写对方从事贸易的行业>}. We deal in this line for several years, and [we are one of the representative exporters in our district|< our competitive prices, superior quality and efficiency have won confidence and goodwill among our business clients >]. In order to expand our products into {South America<请填写与开展贸易的国家或地区>}, [we are writing to you to seek cooperate possibilities|< we are approaching you to establish trade relationship>|< we express our desire to enter into business relations with you >]. We are herewith sending you {a catalog together with a price list for your reference<请填写己方提供的材料>}. [We will appreciate your early reply for cooperation|< We shall be grateful if you will reply at an early date >|< We are anticipating your answer >].<br>\nYours faithfully,<br>\n\"\r\n', null, null, '从中国国际贸易促进会获悉,贵方有意采购电器产品。我公司在这一领域已经营多年，是行业内有代表性的出口商。为了扩展我公司产品在南美的销售，特向贵公司致电询问贸易合作的可能性。在此附上我公司近期产品目录及相关价目表以供你方参考。如果贵公司有意和我们合作，我们将感到非常荣幸。敬盼惠复。<br>');
INSERT INTO `correspondence` VALUES ('64', '要求开证人展证\nA request for an extension of the L/C', '', '', '[We regret to tell you that|<We are sorry to inform you that>] owing to {the strike of seamen, the sailing of S/S “Atlas” scheduled to clear for your port on the 23 of this month has been cancelled<请填写需要展证的原因>}, and accordingly, {no direct steamer from here is available during this month.|<请填写由上述原因造成的结果>}<br> [In these circumstances|<In these circumstances>|<Under such circumstances>|<This being the case>], [we would like to request you to please extend|<we would appreciate your immediate extending>|<it is necessary for us to ask you to make an extension of >|<we have to ask you to extend>] your credit by cable to the following effect:<br> Shipping date: {February 15, 2008<请填写展证后的到货日期>}<br> Expiry date: {End of February, 2008<请填写展证后的有效期>}<br> [Your prompt attention would be appreciated by us.|<It will be much appreciated if you will telegraph the modification as requested.>|<Please cooperate with us and reply soon.>|<Please give us cooperation and reply.>|<We will appreciate your cooperation.>|<Understand our position will be appreciated.>|<Your understanding and cooperation will be appreciated.>]<br> [Yours sincerely,|<Best Regards>|<Yours truly>|<Yours faithfully,>]<br>', '', '', '无');
